args: I'm gonna bust this watermelon\nopen with a stick!
You look even more stunning\nin that than usual, darly-poo!
What's wrong, Estelle? You look angry.
I'm appalled by how badly everyone is\nbehaving. It's even worse than I feared!

That child is jumping into the sea
without warming up, while that man
is preparing to crack open a melon
with a giant stick!
And just LOOK at that couple who can't\nkeep their hands at their sides! Shameful!
Surely I cannot be the only one\nwho feels this way?!
We're at a beach, Estelle. I don't think\nthere's any harm in people letting their\nhair down a little bit.
Sure, some people take it too far,\nbut they just need to be gently corrected.
That's right—and I know JUST\nthe woman to do the correcting!
I must start cracking down on\nall of these disgraceful acts!
Er, that's not exactly what I—
It's time to put things right!
Listen up, everyone! Just because this\nis summer does NOT mean you can act\nin any boorish way you please!
You there! Stretch properly before\nattempting to enter the water!
And you! Don't wave that giant stick\naround! Just open the melon carefully\nlike a normal person!
Uh...but doing it like this is fun.
IS IT FUN IF YOU KILL SOMEONE\nBY ACCIDENT?!
Kindly refrain from unneeded physical\ncontact with others while in public!
WHICH IS BOTH UNNEEDED\nAND PHYSICAL CONTACT!!
Whew! That was hard work,\nbut it seems to be paying off.
Look, I know you have your...foibles,\nbut you've gone too far this time.
Don't you want to go swim?
No. That scary lady will just\nyell at me again...
Guess no one gets to eat\nwatermelon this year...
Your heart is...mostly in the right place,\nbut the beach is where people have fun.
Enforcing behavioral standards that take\nfun away from them doesn't feel right.
In the end, I was the one who\nlet myself get carried away.
I'll go apologize to everyone right now.
I REALLY need to do something about\nhow emotional I get at times.
Don't beat yourself up too much.\nI mean, everyone forgave you, right?
So what else is bothering you?
I fear I'm finding myself unsure about\njust what good behavior actually IS.
I don't believe what I'm saying to everyone\nis wrong. Yet you're right in that stopping\ntheir fun isn't a good solution either.
So what am I to do?
Yeah, that's a tough one. But...
Well, at the very least, I think I know\nwhat you need right now...
No, never mind! What do I need?!
You need to come play with\nus and just forget your cares!
